The paper deals with distributed applications and object state synchronization, which are typical topics in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the Global Object Tracker (GoT) model, which is an object-oriented programming model, and the implementation of GoT in a framework called Spacetime, which are relevant to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also mentions version control systems, which are related to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper's focus on replicated objects and their interfaces is relevant to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Finally, the paper's discussion of constraints and performance analysis is relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
